"After the death of his aunt, Gambian President Jammeh launched a large-scale witch hunt, which was supposed to have been involved in her death, and to try to kill the president himself with black magic."
"He ensued shamans from nearby Guinea to help, who, accompanied by police officers, soldiers and the president's personal bodyguards, forcibly took randomly selected men and women from Gambian villages to the president's farm in Kanilai," Amnesty International said in a report.
On the farm, trapped people had to drink a potion of herbs with hallucinogenic effects, which in addition caused intestinal and kidney problems.
