The WikiLeaks case has two meanings.
On the one hand, an apparent scandal is revealed, a scandal that seems to be a scandal only in the face of the hypocrisy that governs relations between states, citizens and the press.
On the other hand, it speaks of profound changes at international level, and foresches a future dominated by regression.
