The rule that classified documents can only consist of reports already known is fundamental in the dynamics of the secret services, and not just in this century.
When you go to a bookstore dedicated to esoteric literature, you will see that each work repeats (about Graal, the mystery of Rennes-le-Château, the Templars or the Masons) exactly what has already been written in previous works.
Not only because the author of the occult texts does not like to search for new information (he does not even know where to look for reports of non-existent ones), but because those who are engaged in the occult believe only what they already know and what confirms what they have learned before.
